        "title": "fix(sessions): start canonical session title migration",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds canonical session title helpers next to the existing label parser while preserving the legacy label API.\n- Updates `/name` to write a canonical `title` and mirror it to legacy `label` for compatibility.\n- Adds `/name --clear` so slash-command clearing matches the API clear semantics.\n- Adds focused tests for title parsing, legacy label compatibility, title/label mirroring, clearing, and normalized comparisons.\n\n## Scope\n\nThis is the first compatibility step of the session naming cleanup. It intentionally does not yet route `sessions.patch`, `sessions.resolve`, gateway row projection, or transcript `session_info.name` through one complete rename service. Those should be follow-up work once the helper layer is accepted.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior or issue addressed: `/name` no longer writes only the legacy label field. It now writes a canonical title and mirrors it to label so existing selectors and UI paths continue to work. `/name --clear` clears both fields.\n\nReal environment tested: Not run locally from this ChatGPT session. GitHub edits were made through the connector.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\n# Not run in this environment\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/sessions/session-title.test.ts\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: Not locally verified here. The branch contains focused Vitest coverage for the new helpers.\n\nWhat was not tested: Gateway patch/unification, session resolve by label/title, browser UI, TUI refresh, transcript session_info migration, and full OpenClaw runtime behavior.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? Yes. `/name --clear` is added, and `/name <title>` now mirrors a title field to the legacy label field.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? No.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? No.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area? Mixed title/label compatibility while gateway patch and resolve still operate on label.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated? The slash command mirrors title to label and all existing legacy label reads continue to work.\n\nAI-assisted changes: Yes, generated with ChatGPT.",
